  "texts": [
    "The latter include neutral collective modes, which can be interpreted as particle-hole bound states in the TDHF/RPA framework.",
    "These collective modes include the Goldstone modes when |ψ 0 ⟩ breaks a continuous symmetry, and these are guaranteed to be gapless due to the conserving nature of the approximation.",
    "Equations for MA-TBGWe now apply the general formalism of the previous subsections to MA-TBG.",
    "First we define the particle-hole operators with momentum q as k∈mBZ µ,νφ m q,µν (k) d † µ (k + q) dν (k),(88)where µ, ν label the Hartree-Fock orbitals, occupied or unoccupied, with creation operator defined as d † µ (k) = τ as ψ τ as µ (k)ĉ † τ as (k), and m labels the excitation mode.",
    "The particle-hole wavefunctions satisfyφ m q,µν (k) = 0 if n µ (k + q) = n ν (k)."
